(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF1B60CB7C5F924FF00F913" box="[160,226,1710,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[168,1419,181,1859]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—♂HT, northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province, Dong Van district; C–D—PT ♀—ditto HT; E–F—R. latifasciata Leech, ♂Type; B.M. Type NoRh 2682, China, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141965; G–H—R. latifasciata Leech, ♀Cotype; B.M. Type NoRh 2683, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141963" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556620/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE172572FFF1B60CB7F2F97DFD48F87A" blockId="11.[151,1436,1782,1953]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">
For many years, this half-forgotten species was known only from 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF1B60CB4ECF97DFC5BF8CA" box="[905,953,1783,1809]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">type</typeStatus>
specimens collected in Moupin [Baoxing, 
<collectingRegion id="7C6CEB90FFF1B60CB7F2F890FF16F8EE" box="[151,244,1818,1845]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
] (western 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF1B60CB608F890FE50F8EE" box="[365,434,1818,1845]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">China</collectingCountry>
) deposited in NHM: 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF1B60CB5CDF891FD02F8EE" box="[680,736,1819,1845]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Type</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="A8AEEEFBFFF1B60CB58DF891FD1DF8EE" box="[744,767,1819,1845]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, B.M. 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF1B60CB42AF891FC65F8EE" box="[847,903,1819,1845]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Type</typeStatus>
NoRh2682, Moupin, 
<date id="CA1603B2FFF1B60CB3E1F890FB14F8EF" box="[1156,1270,1818,1844]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" value="1890-07">July 1890</date>
; 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF1B60CB261F891FADEF8EE" box="[1284,1340,1819,1845]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Type</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="A8AEEEFBFFF1B60CB221F891FABBF8EE" box="[1348,1369,1819,1845]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
B.M. 
<typeStatus id="61139BD0FFF1B60CB7F2F8B5FF2DF882" box="[151,207,1855,1881]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Type</typeStatus>
NoRh2683, Moupin, 
<date id="CA1603B2FFF1B60CB6AFF8B4FDDBF883" box="[458,569,1854,1880]" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" value="1890-07">July 1890</date>
(
<figureCitation id="269339F7FFF1B60CB52CF8B4FD4FF883" box="[585,685,1854,1880]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[168,1419,181,1859]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ragadia latifasciata cristata Monastyrskii &amp; Vu, subspec. nov. A–B—♂HT, northern Vietnam, Ha Giang province, Dong Van district; C–D—PT ♀—ditto HT; E–F—R. latifasciata Leech, ♂Type; B.M. Type NoRh 2682, China, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141965; G–H—R. latifasciata Leech, ♀Cotype; B.M. Type NoRh 2683, Moupin, Kricheldorf coll., July 1890; BMNH(E) 141963" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5556620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5556620/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Figure 8</figureCitation>
). A female similar to 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF1B60CB4C2F8B5FBA4F883" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[935,1094,1854,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF1B60CB4C2F8B5FBA4F883" box="[935,1094,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">R. latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="DA395883FFF1B60CB243F8B4FF00F8A7" author="Nishimura, M." pageId="11" pageNumber="497" pagination="107 - 116" refId="ref13314" refString="Nishimura, M. (2008) Taxonomic information on the genus Ragadia (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae) in Indo-China. Transactions of the Lepidopterological Society of Japan, 59 (2), 107 - 116." type="journal article" year="2008">Nishimura (2008)</bibRefCitation>
from northern 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF1B60CB6E2F8E8FE04F8A7" box="[391,486,1890,1916]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="7C6CEB90FFF1B60CB696F8E8FD2EF8A6" box="[499,716,1890,1917]" country="Vietnam" name="Ha Giang" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Ha Giang province</collectingRegion>
). It was the first record of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF1B60CB48DF8E9FB66F8A7" authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1891" box="[1000,1156,1890,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifasciata">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF1B60CB48DF8E9FB66F8A7" box="[1000,1156,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">R. latifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="C6BF65E2FFF1B60CB3A0F8E8FACAF8A7" box="[1221,1320,1890,1916]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. However, the taxon was regarded as a form of 
<taxonomicName id="79A85EF1FFF1B60CB54AF80DFD46F87B" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1862" box="[559,676,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Ragadia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crisilda">
<emphasis id="8CDCF960FFF1B60CB54AF80DFD46F87B" box="[559,676,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="497">R. crisilda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
